"""Compact bilingual source copy for Landau episodes 04–10."""
TOPICS = {
4: {"zh": ("自由粒子的拉格朗日量", ["沒有外力時，最簡單的粒子如何運動？", "先把一顆粒子放在一條沒有標記的直線上。", "如果把整個實驗向左或向右平移，物理結果不應該改變。", "因此 L 不能依賴粒子所在的位置，也不能偏愛某個方向。", "它只能看見粒子移動得多快；最簡單的速度量是 v²。", "在低速經典力學裡，L = ½mv²；m 是質量。", "速度越難改變，質量 m 就越大，這正是慣性。", "自由粒子的拉格朗日量，已經把慣性寫進了作用量。"]), "en": ("The Lagrangian of a free particle", ["With no external force, how should the simplest particle move?", "Place one particle on an unmarked straight line.", "If we shift the entire experiment left or right, the physical result should not change.", "So L cannot depend on where the particle is, or favor one direction over another.", "It can only see how fast the particle moves; the simplest speed quantity is v squared.", "At low speeds, classical mechanics gives L = ½mv², where m is the mass.", "The harder it is to change the speed, the larger the mass m: that is inertia.", "The free-particle Lagrangian puts inertia directly into the action."])},
5: {"zh": ("粒子系統的拉格朗日量", ["如果世界裡有很多粒子，整個系統的 L 要怎麼寫？", "彼此不作用時，每個粒子都有自己的動能；總 L 就是各部分的總和。", "有作用時，再加上只依賴相對位置的勢能，L = T − U。", "可加性讓我們能從局部粒子的運動，組合出整個系統的力學。"]), "en": ("The Lagrangian of a system of particles", ["If the world contains many particles, how do we write L for the whole system?", "When particles do not interact, each has its own kinetic energy and the total L is their sum.", "With interactions, we add a potential depending on relative positions: L = T − U.", "Additivity lets local particle motions combine into the mechanics of the whole system."])},
6: {"zh": ("能量：時間均勻性留下的守恆量", ["為什麼有些數字會在運動中保持不變？", "如果物理定律今天和明天完全相同，L 就不顯含時間。", "把 L 對速度的導數乘上速度，再減去 L，得到 E = Σ q̇∂L/∂q̇ − L。", "這個 E 就是能量；時間的均勻性，變成了能量守恆。"]), "en": ("Energy: the conserved quantity from uniform time", ["Why do some quantities stay constant during motion?", "If the laws of physics are the same today and tomorrow, L has no explicit time dependence.", "Multiply each velocity by its derivative of L, then subtract L: E = Σ q̇∂L/∂q̇ − L.", "This E is energy. Uniformity of time becomes conservation of energy."])},
7: {"zh": ("動量：空間均勻性留下的守恆量", ["如果整個空間平移一點，物理實驗會改變嗎？", "不會。空間均勻性表示 L 不在乎整體位置，只在乎相對位置。", "因此對每個座標 q，p = ∂L/∂q̇ 在沒有外力時保持不變。", "動量守恆，就是空間平移對稱性的影子。"]), "en": ("Momentum: the conserved quantity from uniform space", ["Would an experiment change if we shifted the entire laboratory?", "No. Homogeneous space means L cares about relative positions, not the absolute location.", "For each coordinate q, p = ∂L/∂q̇ stays constant when no external force acts.", "Momentum conservation is the shadow of spatial translation symmetry."])},
8: {"zh": ("質心：把整個系統看成一點", ["兩個粒子互相碰撞時，能不能找到一個更簡單的代表點？", "把每個位置乘上它的質量，再除以總質量，就得到質心 R。", "內力成對抵消，所以質心只受到外力：M R̈ = F 外。", "複雜系統的整體平移，可以先由一個質心描述。"]), "en": ("The centre of mass: one point for a whole system", ["When particles collide, can one representative point simplify the picture?", "Multiply each position by its mass and divide by total mass: that gives the centre of mass R.", "Internal forces cancel in pairs, so only external force moves it: M R̈ = F external.", "The translation of a complicated system can be described first by one centre of mass."])},
9: {"zh": ("角動量：旋轉的守恆量", ["直線平移有動量，那旋轉運動有什麼對應的數字？", "從原點到粒子的向量 r，和動量 p 做叉積，得到角動量 M = r × p。", "若外力矩為零，角動量的時間導數就是零。", "旋轉對稱性，留下角動量守恆。"]), "en": ("Angular momentum: the conserved quantity of rotation", ["Linear motion has momentum. What is its counterpart for rotation?", "Take the cross product of position r with momentum p: angular momentum M = r × p.", "When the external torque is zero, its time derivative vanishes.", "Rotational symmetry leaves us conservation of angular momentum."])},
10: {"zh": ("機械相似性：不用重新解一次", ["如果把同一個系統放大，運動還會像原來一樣嗎？", "在一維運動中，L = ½mẋ² − U(x)；能量決定速度沿著勢能曲線前進。", "改變長度、時間與能量的尺度，可以把一條軌跡變成另一條相似軌跡。", "這種機械相似性，讓我們用一個解理解一整族運動。"]), "en": ("Mechanical similarity: solve a whole family at once", ["If we scale the same system up, will its motion still resemble the original?", "For one-dimensional motion, L = ½mẋ² − U(x); energy sets the speed along the potential curve.", "Rescale length, time, and energy, and one trajectory turns into a similar trajectory.", "Mechanical similarity lets one solution explain an entire family of motions."])},
11: {"zh": ("一維運動：從能量讀出軌跡", ["只有一個自由度時，能不能不先解牛頓方程，就知道粒子怎麼走？", "對座標 x，L = ½mẋ² − U(x)，而能量 E = ½mẋ² + U(x) 保持不變。", "因此速度由能量差決定：ẋ = ±√{2[E−U(x)]/m}；只有 U(x) ≤ E 的區域允許運動。", "當 U(x) = E，速度降為零，粒子在轉向點折返；兩個轉向點之間就是有限振盪。"]), "en": ("One-dimensional motion: read the trajectory from energy", ["With only one degree of freedom, can we predict the motion without first solving Newton's equation?", "For coordinate x, L = ½mẋ² − U(x), while the conserved energy is E = ½mẋ² + U(x).", "The energy difference sets the speed: ẋ = ±√{2[E−U(x)]/m}; motion is allowed only where U(x) ≤ E.", "Where U(x) = E, the speed vanishes and the particle turns back; two turning points bound an oscillation."])},
12: {"zh": ("由週期反推勢能井", ["只量到不同能量下的振盪週期，能不能反推出粒子所在的勢能井？", "對每個能量 E，水平線會在兩個轉向點 x₁ 和 x₂ 碰到 U(x)；兩點距離就是振盪寬度。", "阿貝爾反演把週期資料變成寬度：x₂(U) − x₁(U) = [1/(π√{2m})]∫₀ᵁ T(E)/√(U−E) dE。", "週期只能決定勢能井的寬度，不能決定左右形狀；再假設勢能對稱，才得到唯一的 U(x)。"]), "en": ("Reconstructing a potential well from its period", ["If we measure only the oscillation period at different energies, can we reconstruct the particle's potential well?", "For each energy E, a horizontal line meets U(x) at two turning points, x one and x two; their separation is the oscillation width.", "Abel inversion converts period data into width: x₂(U) − x₁(U) = [1/(π√{2m})]∫₀ᵁ T(E)/√(U−E) dE.", "The period fixes the width, but not the separate left and right shapes; assuming a symmetric well makes U(x) unique."])},
13: {"zh": ("約化質量：把兩體變成一體", ["兩個互相作用的粒子，能不能化成一個粒子的運動問題？", "先分離整體質心的平移，再用 r = r₁ − r₂ 描述兩粒子的相對位置。", "相對運動的拉格朗日量是 L = ½μṙ² − U(r)，其中 μ = m₁m₂/(m₁ + m₂) 稱為約化質量。", "因此兩體問題等價於質量 μ 的單一粒子在 U(r) 中運動；求出 r(t)，就能重建兩顆粒子的軌跡。"]), "en": ("Reduced mass: turn two bodies into one", ["Can the motion of two interacting particles be reduced to a one-particle problem?", "First separate the translation of the centre of mass, then use r = r₁ − r₂ for the relative position.", "The relative Lagrangian is L = ½μṙ² − U(r), where μ = m₁m₂/(m₁ + m₂) is the reduced mass.", "The two-body problem is therefore one particle of mass μ moving in U(r); once r(t) is known, both original trajectories follow."])},
14: {"zh": ("中心力場：角動量如何決定軌道", ["當位能只依賴粒子到固定中心的距離 U(r)，力永遠沿半徑方向，這就是中心力場。", "角動量 M = r × p 保持不變，所以半徑向量始終位於垂直 M 的平面內，整條軌道必定是平面的。", "在極座標中 M = mr²φ̇；因此半徑向量在相等時間掃過相等面積，這正是克卜勒第二定律。", "徑向運動可視為一維問題，其有效位能 Ueff(r) = U(r) + M²/(2mr²)；交點 Ueff = E 決定最近與最遠距離。"]), "en": ("Central fields: how angular momentum shapes an orbit", ["When the potential depends only on distance from a fixed centre, U(r), the force is always radial: this is a central field.", "Angular momentum M = r × p is conserved, so the radius vector remains in the plane perpendicular to M and the entire orbit is planar.", "In polar coordinates M = mr²φ̇; the radius vector therefore sweeps out equal areas in equal times, which is Kepler's second law.", "Radial motion becomes a one-dimensional problem with effective potential Ueff(r) = U(r) + M²/(2mr²); intersections with E set the nearest and farthest distances."])},
15: {"zh": ("克卜勒問題：能量決定圓錐軌道", ["萬有引力的位能 U(r) = −α/r，對應平方反比的吸引力；它是最重要的中心力場之一。", "結合能量與角動量守恆，軌道可寫成 p/r = 1 + e cosφ，因此焦點位於力的中心，軌道必是圓錐曲線。", "總能量 E < 0 時是橢圓，E = 0 時是拋物線，E > 0 時是雙曲線；偏心率 e 正好區分這三種情形。", "對束縛的橢圓軌道，週期滿足 T² ∝ a³，而且只由能量、也就是半長軸 a 決定，這就是克卜勒第三定律。"]), "en": ("Kepler's problem: energy selects the conic orbit", ["The gravitational potential U(r) = −α/r produces an attractive inverse-square force, one of the most important central fields.", "Combining conservation of energy and angular momentum gives p/r = 1 + e cosφ, so the force centre is a focus and the orbit is a conic section.", "For total energy E < 0 the orbit is an ellipse, for E = 0 a parabola, and for E > 0 a hyperbola; the eccentricity e distinguishes the three cases.", "For a bound elliptical orbit, T² ∝ a³, and the period depends only on the energy, equivalently the semi-major axis a: Kepler's third law."])},
16: {"zh": ("粒子解體：守恆律預測碎片方向", ["一個靜止粒子自發解體成兩個粒子時，不必知道作用力細節，動量與能量守恆就能預測結果。", "在質心系中，兩個碎片帶著大小相等、方向相反的動量；若解體能為 ε，則 p₀ = √(2με)。", "若母粒子在實驗室中以速度 V 運動，碎片速度只是向量相加 v = V + v₀；質心系的速度球因此整體平移。", "當 V > v₀，碎片只能向前落在一個圓錐內；若最大張角是 θₘₐₓ，則 sin(θₘₐₓ) = v₀ / V。"]), "en": ("Particle disintegration: conservation predicts the fragments", ["When a particle at rest spontaneously splits into two, momentum and energy conservation predict the outcome without details of the interaction.", "In the centre-of-mass frame the fragments have equal and opposite momenta; for disintegration energy ε, their magnitude is p₀ = √(2με).", "If the parent moves through the laboratory with velocity V, each fragment velocity is simply v = V + v₀, translating the centre-of-mass velocity sphere.", "When V > v₀, a fragment can emerge only inside a forward cone. If its maximum angle is θₘₐₓ, then sin(θₘₐₓ) = v₀ / V."])},
17: {"zh": ("彈性碰撞：質心系裡只轉方向", ["彈性碰撞不改變粒子的內部狀態，因此總動量與動能在碰撞前後都保持不變。", "在質心系中，兩粒子的動量始終大小相等、方向相反；碰撞只把這對向量旋轉，長度完全不變。", "回到實驗室系，只要把質心速度 V 加回兩個碰後速度；守恆律決定可能的速度圓，但散射方向仍取決於粒子間作用力。", "若第二粒子起初靜止，它最多取得入射能量的 4m₁m₂/(m₁+m₂)²；兩個質量相等時，能量可以完全轉移。"]), "en": ("Elastic collisions: only direction changes in the centre-of-mass frame", ["An elastic collision leaves the particles' internal states unchanged, so both total momentum and kinetic energy are conserved.", "In the centre-of-mass frame the two momenta remain equal and opposite; the collision merely rotates this pair of vectors without changing their lengths.", "Returning to the laboratory means adding the centre-of-mass velocity V to both final velocities. Conservation fixes a velocity circle, while the interaction selects the scattering direction.", "If the second particle starts at rest, it can receive at most the fraction 4m₁m₂/(m₁+m₂)² of the incident energy; equal masses allow complete transfer."])},
18: {"zh": ("散射：從撞擊參數到截面", ["守恆律只能限制碰撞結果；若要算出粒子究竟偏轉多少，還必須知道中心位能 U(r) 並解出軌道。", "把兩體碰撞化成約化質量 μ 的單粒子問題後，入射軌道由無限遠速度 v∞ 與撞擊參數 b 描述。", "撞擊參數 b 是入射直線與力中心的垂直距離；角動量是 M = μ × b × v∞，能量是 E = (1/2) × μ × v∞²。", "粒子先接近中心，在最近距離 rₘᵢₙ 轉向後離開；軌道的對稱性把入射與出射漸近線連到散射角 χ。", "不同的 b 對應不同的 χ：小撞擊參數通常靠中心更近、偏轉更大，大撞擊參數則幾乎沿原方向前進。", "對均勻粒子束，落在 b 到 b + db 圓環內的粒子數與面積 2π × b × db 成正比，因此散射截面 dσ = 2π × b × db。", "把 b 寫成 χ 的函數，就得到微分截面 dσ/dΩ = [b / sin(χ)] × |db/dχ|；它把可測的角分布直接連回作用位能。"]), "en": ("Scattering: from impact parameter to cross-section", ["Conservation laws only constrain a collision. To calculate the actual deflection, we must know the central potential U(r) and solve the orbit.", "After reducing the two-body collision to one particle of reduced mass μ, the incoming orbit is described by its speed at infinity v∞ and impact parameter b.", "The impact parameter b is the perpendicular distance from the incoming line to the force centre, giving M = μ × b × v∞ and E = (1/2) × μ × v∞².", "The particle approaches the centre, turns at its closest distance rₘᵢₙ, and escapes. Orbit symmetry connects the incoming and outgoing asymptotes to the scattering angle χ.", "Different values of b produce different χ: a small impact parameter usually means a closer encounter and larger deflection, while a large b gives almost straight motion.", "For a uniform beam, particles between b and b + db occupy an annulus of area 2π × b × db, defining the cross-section dσ = 2π × b × db.", "Writing b as a function of χ gives dσ/dΩ = [b / sin(χ)] × |db/dχ|. This differential cross-section links the measured angular distribution back to the interaction potential."])},
19: {"zh": ("拉塞福公式：庫侖力的散射指紋", ["現在把散射理論用在庫侖位能 U(r) = α / r；α 的正負分別代表排斥或吸引，但力的大小都依平方反比衰減。", "對約化質量 μ、無限遠速度 v∞ 與撞擊參數 b，解出雙曲線軌道後可得 b = [α / (μ × v∞²)] × cot(χ / 2)。", "這個關係很直觀：b 越大，粒子離中心越遠，散射角 χ 越小；要產生大角度偏轉，就必須非常靠近力中心。", "把 b(χ) 代入一般截面公式，得到 dσ/dΩ = [α / (2 × μ × v∞²)]² / sin⁴(χ / 2)，這就是拉塞福散射公式。", "最醒目的特徵是 sin⁻⁴(χ / 2)：小角度事件極多，而大角度散射雖然稀少，卻提供最直接的近距離結構資訊。", "公式只含 α²，所以把庫侖力從排斥改成吸引不會改變角分布；軌道彎向相反方向，但相同角度的事件數一致。", "若散射中心遠重於入射粒子，μ 幾乎等於入射質量；測量 dσ/dΩ 隨角度與能量的變化，就能檢驗平方反比定律與中心電荷。"]), "en": ("Rutherford's formula: the fingerprint of Coulomb scattering", ["Apply scattering theory to the Coulomb potential U(r) = α / r. The sign of α distinguishes repulsion from attraction, while the force magnitude follows an inverse-square law.", "For reduced mass μ, speed at infinity v∞, and impact parameter b, the hyperbolic orbit gives b = [α / (μ × v∞²)] × cot(χ / 2).", "The relation is intuitive: a larger b keeps the particle farther from the centre and produces a smaller scattering angle χ; large deflections require a close encounter.", "Substituting b(χ) into the general cross-section gives dσ/dΩ = [α / (2 × μ × v∞²)]² / sin⁴(χ / 2), Rutherford's scattering formula.", "Its striking signature is sin⁻⁴(χ / 2): small-angle events are abundant, while rare large-angle events carry the clearest information about short-distance structure.", "Only α² appears, so changing the Coulomb force from repulsive to attractive does not change the angular distribution. The orbit bends the other way, but the event count is identical.", "When the scattering centre is much heavier than the projectile, μ is nearly the projectile mass. Measuring dσ/dΩ versus angle and energy tests the inverse-square law and central charge."])},
20: {"zh": ("小角度散射：用微擾法直接算偏轉", ["當撞擊參數 b 很大、位能很弱時，粒子只被輕輕推偏；這種小角度散射可以直接用微擾法計算，而且在實驗室系就能完成。", "把 x 軸取在入射動量方向；偏轉很小時，散射角約等於垂直方向獲得的動量除以入射動量，而入射動量是質量乘上無限遠速度。", "這個垂直動量，來自整段路徑上的橫向力對時間的積分，沿粒子的直線軌跡慢慢累積。", "因為這個積分本身已經很小，可以假設粒子沿直線等速前進；橫向力就是位能的徑向梯度乘上一個幾何因子，時間則換成沿路徑的位移。", "再把對 x 的積分換成對 r 的積分，就得到一條只依撞擊參數與位能的散射角公式。", "這條公式最實用的地方是：只要知道位能，不必解出完整軌道，就能算出散射角如何隨撞擊參數變化。", "最後把它代回一般截面公式，就得到小角度區的微分截面，這正是弱場散射最實用的近似。"]), "en": ("Small-angle scattering: deflection by perturbation", ["When the impact parameter b is large, the potential is weak and the particle is barely nudged; such small-angle scattering follows directly from perturbation, in the laboratory frame.", "Take the x-axis along the incident momentum; for a small deflection the scattering angle is roughly the transverse momentum gained divided by the incident momentum, which is mass times the speed at infinity.", "That transverse momentum is the time integral of the sideways force, built up along the particle's straight-line path.", "Since the integral is already small, we let the particle move straight at constant speed; the sideways force is the radial gradient of the potential times a geometric factor, and time turns into displacement along the path.", "Converting the x-integral into an r-integral then gives a scattering angle that depends only on the impact parameter and the potential.", "The real payoff is that knowing the potential alone yields the scattering angle as a function of impact parameter, without ever solving the full orbit.", "Substituting it back into the general cross-section gives the differential cross-section at small angles, the most useful weak-field approximation."])},
21: {"zh": ("一維自由振盪：每個穩定平衡都是簡諧", ["力學系統最常見的運動之一，就是在穩定平衡附近的小振盪；我們先看最簡單的一個自由度。", "穩定平衡對應位能的極小值；在附近把位能展開，最低階就是一個二次項，係數 k 正是位能在該點的二階導數。", "動能近似為二分之一 m 乘上速度平方，於是這個系統的拉格朗日量就是動能減位能。", "代入運動方程，得到一條線性方程：質量乘加速度，加上 k 乘位移等於零，也就是加速度正比於負的位移。", "它的解是一個簡諧振盪：位移隨時間做餘弦擺動，振幅是 a，相位裡的 α 是初相位。", "關鍵是角頻率只由系統本身決定：等於根號 k 除以 m，和振幅、初始條件都無關。", "總能量是動能加位能，算出來正比於振幅的平方，等於二分之一 m 乘上角頻率平方再乘上振幅平方。"]), "en": ("Free oscillations in one dimension: every stable equilibrium is harmonic", ["One of the most common motions in mechanics is a small oscillation about a stable equilibrium; we begin with the simplest case, a single degree of freedom.", "Stable equilibrium sits at a minimum of the potential energy; expanding around it, the leading term is quadratic, with coefficient k equal to the second derivative there.", "The kinetic energy is approximately one-half m times velocity squared, so the Lagrangian of the system is the kinetic minus the potential energy.", "Putting this into the equation of motion gives a linear equation: mass times acceleration plus k times displacement equals zero, so the acceleration is proportional to minus the displacement.", "Its solution is a harmonic oscillation: the displacement swings as a cosine in time, with amplitude a and an initial phase alpha.", "The key point is that the angular frequency is fixed by the system alone: it is the square root of k over m, independent of amplitude or initial conditions.", "The total energy is kinetic plus potential, and it works out proportional to the amplitude squared, equal to one-half m times angular frequency squared times amplitude squared."])},
22: {"zh": ("受迫振盪與共振", ["一個原本會自由振盪的系統，如果再受到一個隨時間變化的外力，運動會怎麼改變？", "在運動方程的右邊加上這個外力：質量乘加速度，加上 k 乘位移，等於外力 F(t)。", "最重要的情形是週期性外力：F(t) 以固定的驅動頻率 γ 做餘弦振盪。", "穩定之後，系統會跟著驅動頻率 γ 擺動，振幅正比於一除以固有頻率平方減驅動頻率平方。", "當驅動頻率接近固有頻率 ω，這個分母趨近於零，振幅急速放大，這就是共振。", "剛好落在共振點上，振幅不再有限，而是隨時間線性成長：位移像一個越長越大的正弦波。", "所以一般運動是兩部分疊加：系統自己的自由振盪，加上被外力牽著走的受迫振盪。"]), "en": ("Forced oscillations and resonance", ["If a system that would freely oscillate is also driven by a time-varying external force, how does its motion change?", "We add that force to the right-hand side of the equation of motion: mass times acceleration plus k times displacement equals the force F(t).", "The most important case is a periodic force: F(t) oscillates as a cosine at a fixed driving frequency gamma.", "After it settles, the system swings at the driving frequency gamma, with an amplitude proportional to one over the natural frequency squared minus the driving frequency squared.", "As the driving frequency approaches the natural frequency omega, that denominator tends to zero and the amplitude grows sharply: this is resonance.", "Exactly at resonance the amplitude is no longer finite but grows linearly in time: the displacement looks like a sine wave that keeps getting taller.", "So the general motion is a sum of two parts: the system's own free oscillation, plus the forced oscillation dragged along by the external force."])},
23: {"zh": ("多自由度振盪：簡正模態", ["前面談的是單一自由度；如果系統有很多個自由度、而且彼此耦合，運動看起來會很複雜。", "但在穩定平衡附近，動能和位能都能寫成座標的二次型，拉格朗日量就是這兩者的差。", "一樣假設每個座標都按同一個頻率 ω 做指數振盪，代入後得到一組線性代數方程。", "要有非零解，係數的行列式必須為零；這個特徵方程的根，就是系統的固有頻率。", "每個固有頻率對應一個簡正模態；第一個是同相模態：兩個質量一起往同方向擺動，頻率較低。", "第二個是反相模態：兩個質量往相反方向擺動，中間的彈簧被拉得更緊，所以頻率較高。", "一般運動就是這些簡正模態的疊加；在簡正座標下，每個模態各自獨立地簡諧振盪。"]), "en": ("Oscillations with several degrees of freedom: normal modes", ["So far we treated one degree of freedom; when a system has many coupled degrees of freedom, the motion can look complicated.", "But near stable equilibrium both the kinetic and the potential energy are quadratic forms in the coordinates, and the Lagrangian is their difference.", "Again we assume every coordinate oscillates at the same frequency omega, which turns the equations into a set of linear algebraic equations.", "For a non-zero solution the determinant of the coefficients must vanish; the roots of this characteristic equation are the system's eigenfrequencies.", "Each eigenfrequency gives a normal mode; the first is the in-phase mode, where the two masses swing together in the same direction, at the lower frequency.", "The second is the out-of-phase mode, where the masses swing in opposite directions, stretching the middle spring more, so the frequency is higher.", "The general motion is a superposition of these normal modes; in normal coordinates each mode oscillates independently and harmonically."])},
24: {"zh": ("分子振動：從自由度到簡正模態", ["分子裡的原子不只會在平衡位置附近振動；整個分子還能平移和轉動。", "n 個原子共有 3n 個自由度；扣掉 3 個平移和 3 個轉動，剩下 3n−6 個才是振動。", "直線分子是例外：繞著分子軸的轉動沒有意義，只有 2 個轉動自由度，所以有 3n−5 個振動。", "要分離出振動，就令總動量為零讓質心固定，再令總角動量為零把整體轉動去掉。", "以直線三原子分子為例；第一個簡正模態是對稱伸縮：兩端原子對稱地一起進出，中間原子不動。", "第二個是反對稱伸縮：兩端原子往同一方向移動，中間原子往反方向移動，頻率比較高。", "第三個是彎曲模態：原子垂直於軸擺動、讓分子彎折；它在兩個互相垂直的平面裡簡併，對應兩個相同的頻率。"]), "en": ("Vibrations of molecules: counting and normal modes", ["The atoms in a molecule do not only vibrate about equilibrium; the whole molecule can also translate and rotate.", "With n atoms there are 3n degrees of freedom; removing 3 translations and 3 rotations leaves 3n − 6 vibrations.", "A linear molecule is the exception: rotation about the molecular axis is meaningless, leaving only 2 rotations and therefore 3n − 5 vibrations.", "To isolate the vibrations we set the total momentum to zero, fixing the centre of mass, and the total angular momentum to zero, removing overall rotation.", "Take a linear triatomic molecule; the first normal mode is the symmetric stretch, where the outer atoms move in and out together while the centre stays still.", "The second is the antisymmetric stretch, where the outer atoms move the same way and the centre moves opposite, at a higher frequency.", "The third is the bending mode, where the atoms move across the axis and the molecule bends; it is doubly degenerate, one for each of two perpendicular planes."])},
25: {"zh": ("阻尼振盪：在介質中衰減的振動", ["前面都假設運動發生在真空中；真實的振子會受到介質的阻力，能量會慢慢耗散成熱。", "對小振盪，阻力可近似為正比於速度；把它加進運動方程再除以質量，就得到阻尼振盪方程。", "一樣代入指數解，得到特徵方程；它的根是負 λ 加減一個平方根，決定了系統的行為。", "當阻尼較小、λ 小於 ω₀ 時，根是複數：運動仍是簡諧振盪，但振幅以 e 的負 λt 次方指數衰減。", "因為振幅平方正比於能量，系統的平均能量以 e 的負 2λt 次方衰減。", "當阻尼很強、λ 大於 ω₀ 時，兩個根都是負實數：運動不再振盪，而是非週期地慢慢回到平衡。", "剛好在臨界阻尼、λ 等於 ω₀ 時，系統以不振盪的方式最快回到平衡；這就是三種阻尼行為。"]), "en": ("Damped oscillations: decay in a medium", ["So far we assumed motion in a vacuum; a real oscillator feels resistance from the medium, and its energy is gradually dissipated as heat.", "For small oscillations the friction is approximately proportional to velocity; adding it to the equation of motion and dividing by the mass gives the damped-oscillator equation.", "Substituting an exponential solution gives the characteristic equation, whose roots are minus lambda plus or minus a square root that decides the behaviour.", "For weak damping, lambda less than omega-zero, the roots are complex: the motion is a harmonic oscillation whose amplitude decays as e to the minus lambda t.", "Since the squared amplitude is proportional to energy, the mean energy decays as e to the minus two lambda t.", "For strong damping, lambda greater than omega-zero, both roots are real and negative: the motion no longer oscillates but returns to equilibrium aperiodically.", "Exactly at critical damping, lambda equal to omega-zero, the system returns to equilibrium as fast as possible without oscillating; these are the three regimes of damping."])},
26: {"zh": ("有阻尼的受迫振盪與共振曲線", ["把一個週期性外力加到有阻尼的振子上；運動方程的右邊，就多了一項 f cos(γt) 除以質量，等於把受迫振盪和阻尼合在一起。", "過渡項會隨時間指數衰減掉，經過一段時間後只剩下穩態：系統以驅動頻率 γ 持續振盪。", "這個穩態振幅 b 會隨驅動頻率而變，由一個同時含有頻率差與阻尼 λ 的分母決定。", "和無阻尼的情形不同，阻尼讓分母永遠不為零，所以共振峰不再發散、而是有限的，峰值大約落在固有頻率 ω₀ 附近。", "關鍵在於阻尼的大小：阻尼越小，分母在共振處就越小，共振峰也就越高、越尖。", "峰的尖銳程度可以用品質因子 Q 來衡量，它等於 ω₀ 除以 2λ；阻尼越小，Q 越大、共振也越尖銳。", "此外，振盪總是落後外力一個相位；遠低於共振時幾乎同相，遠高於共振時接近反相，而在共振點恰好落後 90 度，阻尼把這個相位跳變抹平。"]), "en": ("Forced oscillations with friction: the resonance curve", ["We now drive the damped oscillator with a periodic force; the right-hand side of the equation gains a term f cos(gamma t) divided by the mass, combining forced motion with friction.", "The transient part decays away exponentially, so after some time only the steady state remains: the system oscillates at the driving frequency gamma.", "This steady amplitude b varies with the driving frequency, set by a denominator that contains both the frequency mismatch and the damping lambda.", "Unlike the frictionless case, damping keeps the denominator from ever reaching zero, so the resonance peak is finite instead of infinite, and it sits close to the natural frequency omega-zero.", "The key is the amount of damping: the smaller the damping, the smaller the denominator at resonance, and the taller and sharper the peak.", "The sharpness of the peak is measured by the quality factor Q, equal to omega-zero over two lambda; less damping means a larger Q and a sharper resonance.", "The oscillation also always lags the force by a phase; far below resonance they are nearly in phase, far above nearly opposite, and exactly at resonance the lag is ninety degrees, with friction smoothing the jump."])},
27: {"zh": ("參數共振：週期性改變參數就能激振", ["有一種系統不靠外力驅動，只要週期性地改變它自己的參數，就能被激發起振盪；盪鞦韆就是最好的例子。", "這類系統的運動方程是 ẍ + ω²(t) x = 0，其中頻率 ω 會隨時間週期性地變化。", "最重要的情形是頻率被輕微地週期調變：ω²(t) = ω₀²(1 + h cos(γt))，其中 h 很小。", "參數共振最強的條件很特別：調變頻率要接近固有頻率的兩倍，也就是 γ 約等於 2ω₀。", "這時平衡點變得不穩定：任何微小擾動都會讓振幅以指數成長，x 正比於 e 的 st 次方，這和普通共振只線性成長很不一樣。", "成長率與共振範圍都由 h 決定：不穩定帶落在 2ω₀ 的兩側，半寬大約是二分之一 h ω₀，帶寬和成長率都正比於 h。", "摩擦會對抗它：淨成長變成 e 的 s 減 λ 乘 t 次方，所以成長率 s 必須大於阻尼 λ 才會發生，阻尼也讓不穩定帶變窄。"]), "en": ("Parametric resonance: exciting a system by changing its parameters", ["Some systems are excited not by an external force but simply by varying their own parameters periodically; pumping a swing is the classic example.", "The equation of motion for such a system is x-double-dot plus omega-squared-of-t times x equals zero, where the frequency omega varies periodically in time.", "The most important case is a small periodic modulation of the frequency: omega-squared of t equals omega-zero-squared times one plus h cosine gamma t, with h small.", "Parametric resonance is strongest under a special condition: the modulation frequency must be near twice the natural frequency, gamma close to two omega-zero.", "Then the equilibrium becomes unstable: any tiny disturbance makes the amplitude grow exponentially, x proportional to e to the s t, unlike ordinary resonance which grows only linearly.", "The growth rate and the resonance range are both set by h: the unstable band lies on either side of two omega-zero with a half-width of about one half h omega-zero, both width and growth proportional to h.", "Friction opposes it: the net growth becomes e to the s minus lambda times t, so the growth rate s must exceed the damping lambda, and friction also narrows the unstable band."])},
28: {"zh": ("非簡諧振盪：頻率會隨振幅改變", ["之前的小振盪理論只保留了位能與動能的二次項；如果再保留更高次的項，就進入非簡諧、也就是非線性振盪。", "把拉格朗日量展開到三次、四次項，就多了 x³ 和 x⁴ 這些非簡諧項。", "對應的運動方程右邊也不再是零，而是出現 −αx² − βx³ 這些非線性項。", "我們用逐次逼近法求解：先取最低階的 x = a cos(ωt)，再一項一項修正。", "第一個新現象：運動不再是純正弦；非線性項會生出倍頻，也就是 2ω、3ω 的泛音，波形因此變形。", "第二個、也是最重要的新現象：振盪的頻率會隨振幅改變，ω 等於 ω₀ 加上 κ 乘 a 平方。", "所以振幅越大，頻率偏移越多；不同振幅的振子會漸漸失去同步，這正是非線性振盪的招牌特徵。"]), "en": ("Anharmonic oscillations: frequency depends on amplitude", ["The small-oscillation theory kept only the quadratic terms of the potential and kinetic energy; keeping higher terms gives anharmonic, or non-linear, oscillations.", "Expanding the Lagrangian to third and fourth order adds anharmonic terms in x-cubed and x-to-the-fourth.", "The equation of motion then gains non-linear terms on the right: minus alpha x-squared minus beta x-cubed.", "We solve by successive approximation: start from the lowest order, x equals a cosine omega t, then correct it term by term.", "The first new effect: the motion is no longer a pure sine; the non-linear terms generate overtones at two omega and three omega, so the waveform is distorted.", "The second and most important effect: the oscillation frequency now depends on the amplitude, omega equals omega-zero plus kappa a-squared.", "So the larger the amplitude, the larger the frequency shift; oscillators of different amplitude gradually fall out of step, the hallmark of non-linear oscillation."])},
}

